      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The absence of Keayang Zahara gives JILLIBY BALLERINI (6) her shot at a well-deserved Group 1 win. She has been runner-up to her star stablemate four times so far this campaign including last week's rich TAB Trot in NZ. Has still managed to win five times this prep including the Terang Cup from a 30m handicap two back. She hasn't missed a place in seven tries at this circuit and distance, winning three of them. Her form stands out in this line up. JILLIBY DREAMLOVER (1) has had eight weeks off since fading out of the Grand Prix last start but put together a string of wins and placings prior including a Great Southern Star third from this barrier two back and she strikes at 50 per cent here. Multiple Group 1 winner ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (3) is ticking along well with wins the last two times she raced here, both from wider barriers than this. Last season's star filly TRACY THE JET (7) will be fitter for the fresh effort when midfield after racing wide against the boys. She can improve.",
